we saw if we have some new changes on server
we need fetch to bring those commits
and then we need a merge (can be ff or three way merge)
to getting our working directory updated.

git combine these steps and create "PULL" command
it will fetch and merge
so we can have conflict on pulling (because it can make a MERGE!)
PULL = FETCH + MERGE

              MAIN
               |
               v
+------+    +------+
| C1   |<---| C2   |
+------+    +------+
               ^
               |
          origin/main


Note: we should set the merge as default (it was default on older version)
      "git config pull.rebase false"

                                             MAIN
                                              |
                                              v
      +------+    +------+    +------+    +------+
      | C1   |<---| C2   |<---| C3   |<---| merge|    Note: we have some local commit as c3
      +------+    +------+    +------+    +------+          we have B1,b2 on server
                         ^                   |              we make the pull by a three way merge
                         |                   |              "git pull"      //when merge is default
                      +------+    +------+   |
                      | B1   |<---| B2   |<--|
                      +------+    +------+
                                     ^
                                     |
                                 origin/main


Note: we can use rebasing instead merge
      to create a linear history, it depend on us!


+------+    +------+    +------+                     Note: we have some local commit as c3
| C1   |<---| C2   |<---| C3   |                           we have B1,b2 on server
+------+    +------+    +------+      MAIN                 we make the pull by rebasing
                           ^           |                   "git pull --rebase"
                           |           v
                        +------+    +------+
                        | B1   |<---| B2   |
                        +------+    +------+
                                       ^
                                       |
                                    origin/main


1. we commit this file at end of step 2.
   so we have a commit that not exist on server

2. we delete the "extraFile" manually on github
   and make a commit there, so we have a commit on server
   that not exist on local!

3. because we set merge as default for puling,
   when pull it make a three way merge (due to diverge we have)

   "git pull"           //it opened a commit massage
                        *   f25d2d8 (HEAD -> main) Merge branch 'main' of github.com:sinafadaie/Git
                        |\
                        | * 901c5e9 (origin/main, origin/HEAD) Delete extraFile
                        * | e82dca1 pulling
                        * | dffd88d fetch
                        |/
                        * da5f8bc Create some extraFile
                        * 243f38f git ignore


Note: we can use the rebase option.             "git pull -- rebase"
      if we used pull   by rebasing
      the graph gonna be like:

       * 901c5e9 (HEAD -> main,origin/main, origin/HEAD) Delete extraFile       //we don't have merge commit any more
      /
     *  e82dca1 pulling
     *  dffd88d fetch
     |
     * da5f8bc Create some extraFile
